Title: Why CIELAB doesn’t improve median cut
Description:
Color quantization is a process that compresses an image into a color table, or a palette, and an index image that references the palette.
The process can be divided into a palette design phase that analyzes an image, followed by a pixel mapping phase that assigns a palette color to each original image pixel.
